# Redesign: DuoTrak-Aware AI Goal Chat

## Problem

The current AI chat is a **generic slot-filler** that knows nothing about DuoTrak. It robotically asks for 6 fields ([intent](file:///c:/Users/Kevin/Projects/personal_projects/DuoTrak_v1.1/backend/app/services/goal_chat/slot_tracker.py#20-25), `success_definition`, `availability`, `time_budget`, `accountability_mode`, `tasks`) with no understanding of partner accountability, proof types, or DuoTrak's unique value.

## What DuoTrak Actually Is

DuoTrak is **partner accountability** — you're accountable to a *real person*, not code or AI. The chat AI must understand:

| Accountability Type | Use Case | How It Works |
|---|---|---|
| **📸 Photo proof** | Gym, cooking, cleaning, projects | Partner sends photo evidence |
| **🎥 Video proof** | Workouts, practice sessions | Partner sends video evidence |
| **🎙️ Voice reflection** | Reading, learning, journaling | Voice note summarizing what you learned |
| **⏰ Check-in window** | Wake up at 7am, medication, hydration | Time-triggered, small window to confirm |
| **✅ Task completion** | General tasks, milestones | Mark as done, partner reviews |

## Proposed Change

Replace the rigid slot-filling system with a **two-phase AI approach**:

### Phase 1: Natural Conversation (what changes)
The AI has a rich system prompt that understands DuoTrak. Instead of asking "What's your accountability mode?", it naturally suggests the right one based on context.

> **User**: "I want to learn Python in 3 months"
> **AI**: "Great! How many hours a week can you dedicate? And would you prefer **voice reflections** after study sessions so your partner can hear what you've learned, or **photo proof** of completed exercises?"

### Phase 2: AI-Generated Summary (what changes)
When the conversation has enough info, the AI produces a **structured summary** (JSON) that includes the required planning fields plus a rich narrative.

